{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nAfter dropping the bot + FFO, EVERY doc/reference to autosubmit, the auto-lander, or the FFO Gerrit workflow becomes inaccurate. This is a comprehensive sweep, not just the top-level guides.\n\n## What — comprehensive grep-driven sweep\nSweep the whole repo (docs/, top-level *.md, inline help text / code comments, runbooks) for and correct/remove every reference to the old model. Search terms (case-insensitive): 'autosubmit', 'auto-lander'/'autolander', 'land-contract'/'land_contract', 'land-status', 'lander_down', 'fast forward only'/'fast-forward-only'/'FFO', 'rebase[- ]on[- ]behalf', 'Autosubmit label', 'set Autosubmit', the 'both votes green != lands' trap language, and the 'land <change> --wait' flow.\n\nTargets include (non-exhaustive; grep is source of truth):\n- CLAUDE.md (Git workflow / land-through-Gerrit section), CLAUDE.local.md (local land guidance).\n- CONTRIBUTING.md (steps 1-5 land flow, the lander_down fallback, feature-branch merge-carry references to FFO).\n- docs/your-first-change.md, README.md (landing pointer), docs/land-contract.md (delete/redirect).\n- docs/gerrit-aws-setup.md, docs/two-vote-gate-rollback.md, docs/releasing.md, review-bot docs, any workflow/*.md — anywhere the Gerrit submit/land flow is described.\n- Inline: CLI --help text, script comments, project.config comments.\n\n## New model to document everywhere\nLand via a plain Gerrit **Submit** once **LLM-Review+1 AND Verified+1**; Gerrit rebases-and-submits server-side (Rebase-If-Necessary); on a **textual** conflict, git fetch && git rebase origin/main, re-push, re-Submit. **There is no bot, no Autosubmit label, no land command.** Post-merge main CI + manual revert is the bounded-risk safety net.\n\n## ADR history\nDo NOT rewrite ADR 0040/0042 prose (they are historical records) — instead add a '> Superseded by ADR 0047' banner at the top of each.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A fresh grep for the search terms above returns only (a) historical ADRs with a supersession banner, and (b) ADR 0047 itself — no live guidance still describes autosubmit / the auto-lander / FFO-must-rebase as the current flow.\n- [ ] CLAUDE.md, CLAUDE.local.md, CONTRIBUTING.md, your-first-change.md, README.md landing sections describe the Submit-when-green / Gerrit-rebases model.\n- [ ] ADR 0040 + 0042 carry a 'Superseded by ADR 0047' banner.\n- [ ] Any CLI --help / drift-gated command+MCP reference docs regenerate clean after the land command is removed (coordinate with the retire-code story)."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783986551969576001,"uuid":"001c849b-ddbe-4ca3-8fb1-2630740e9fd9"}